When Kubernetes creates a Pod it assigns one of these QoS classes to the Pod:

Guaranteed
Burstable
BestEffort


#For a Pod to be given a QoS class of Guaranteed:

#Every Container in the Pod must have a memory limit and a memory request, and they must be the same.
#Every Container in the Pod must have a CPU limit and a CPU request, and they must be the same.



apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: qos-demo
  namespace: qos-example
spec:
  containers:
  - name: qos-demo-ctr
    image: nginx
    resources:
      limits:
        memory: "200Mi"
        cpu: "700m"
      requests:
        memory: "200Mi"
        cpu: "700m"
        
        
        
$kubectl create namespace qos-example


$kubectl get pod qos-demo --namespace=qos-example --output=yaml

You will see guaranteed


A Pod is given a QoS class of Burstable if:

The Pod does not meet the criteria for QoS class Guaranteed.
At least one Container in the Pod has a memory or CPU request.


apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: qos-demoz
  namespace: qos-example
spec:
  containers:
  - name: qos-demo-ctr
    image: nginx
    resources:
      limits:
        memory: "100Mi"
        cpu: "600m"
      requests:
        memory: "200Mi"
        cpu: "700m"
        
      $kubectl create namespace qos-example


$kubectl get pod qos-demoz --namespace=qos-example --output=yaml
  
        
        
you will see burst
Note:Â If a Container specifies its own memory limit, but does not specify a memory request, Kubernetes automatically assigns a memory request that matches the limit. Similarly, if a Container specifies its own CPU limit, but does not specify a CPU request, Kubernetes automatically assigns a CPU request that matches the limit.


For a Pod to be given a QoS class of BestEffort, the Containers in the Pod must not have any memory or CPU limits or requests.
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: qos-demoxz
  namespace: qos-example
spec:
  containers:
  - name: qos-demo-ctr
    image: nginx
   
   
   
        
$kubectl create namespace qos-example


$kubectl get pod qos-demoxz --namespace=qos-example --output=yaml

You will See BestEffort.

#Detailed info about pod 

$kubectl get pod qos-demoz --output=yaml --namespace=qos-example

$kubectl get pods --namespace=qos-example

